Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 475 degrees. Take @cream cheese{3%ounce} out of refrigerator to soften. Halve, peel, and finely chop @yellow onion{1}. Roughly chop @spinach{5%ounce}. Drain and rinse @black beans{1%14oz box}.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add @ground turkey{20%ounce} and @fajita spice blend{2%tablespoon}, breaking up meat into pieces. Season with salt and pepper. Cook until no longer pink, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir @diced tomatoes{14%ounce} and spinach into pan. Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened, ~{2-4%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Meanwhile, add cream cheese and beans to a #medium bowl{}. Mash with a #potato masher{} or fork until mostly smooth. Season with salt and pepper.

Spread bean mixture in an even layer onto one side of each @flour tortillas{4}. Divide turkey mixture between each, then roll up tortillas like wraps.

> TIP: If you can't fit all of the turkey inside, that's OK.

Place burritos in a #baking dish{} seam-side down.

> TIP: If you have extra turkey, or if some of it spills out, sprinkle it around the
> burritos in the dish.

Sprinkle @cheddar cheese{1%cup} over top. Bake in oven until cheese is melted and burritos are warmed through, ~{4-5%minutes}.

While burritos bake, roughly chop @cilantro{1/2%ounce} and cut @lime{1} into wedges. Once burritos are finished, sprinkle cilantro over top of dish. Divide burritos between plates and serve with lime wedges on the side for squeezing over.